<subSubSection id="C325652C47566C029D811A7C08BA7AAC" lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B8036A747566C039D811A7C0DAF7E20" blockId="42.[151,1437,1050,2013]" box="[199,1188,1086,1113]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="B94BEAB547566C039D811A7C08527E21" bold="true" box="[199,345,1086,1112]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Description.</emphasis>
Female (
<figureCitation id="13042A2247566C039C871A7C0B187E21" box="[449,531,1086,1112]" captionStart="FIGURE 27" captionStartId="43.[151,250,1835,1859]" captionTargetBox="[153,1435,453,1812]" captionTargetId="figure-113@43.[153,1435,453,1812]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURE 27. Campoplex exareola sp. nov., female, habitus." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5654011" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5654011/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) 
<typeStatus id="5484880547566C039F641A7C0B837E21" box="[546,648,1086,1112]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">holotype</typeStatus>
. Body length 
<quantity id="4CC79B4247566C039E651A7C0A707E20" box="[803,891,1086,1113]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
, fore wing length 
<quantity id="4CC79B4247566C0399001A7C0D947E20" box="[1094,1183,1086,1113]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.6" pageId="42" pageNumber="43" unit="mm" value="3.6">3.6 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8036A747566C039D811A200C1C7F49" blockId="42.[151,1437,1050,2013]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="B94BEAB547566C039D811A2008057E05" bold="true" box="[199,270,1122,1148]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Head.</emphasis>
Antenna with 24 flagellomeres; first flagellomere 1.25× longer than second flagellomere. Face (
<figureCitation id="13042A2247566C0398291A2009CD7ED9" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-24@44.[178,1409,181,1939]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 28. Campoplex exareola sp. nov., female. A, fore wing; B, mesopleuron; C, propodeum; D, ovipositor; E, head, anterior view; F, head, dorsal view; G, mesoscutum; H, first metasomal segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5654013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5654013/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 28E</figureCitation>
) granulose. Clypeus (
<figureCitation id="13042A2247566C039CFC1AC40B167ED9" box="[442,541,1158,1184]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-24@44.[178,1409,181,1939]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 28. Campoplex exareola sp. nov., female. A, fore wing; B, mesopleuron; C, propodeum; D, ovipositor; E, head, anterior view; F, head, dorsal view; G, mesoscutum; H, first metasomal segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5654013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5654013/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 28E</figureCitation>
) granulose, not convex, apical margin slightly arched and thick medially. Malar space granulose, 0.65× basal width of mandible. Mandible with a very weak lamella basally, upper tooth equal to the length of lower tooth. Frons granulose, median carina absent. Vertex granulose. Interocellar distance (
<figureCitation id="13042A2247566C0399BD1A8C0C577E91" box="[1275,1372,1230,1256]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-24@44.[178,1409,181,1939]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 28. Campoplex exareola sp. nov., female. A, fore wing; B, mesopleuron; C, propodeum; D, ovipositor; E, head, anterior view; F, head, dorsal view; G, mesoscutum; H, first metasomal segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5654013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5654013/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 28F</figureCitation>
) 1.3× ocello-ocular distance and 1.5× distance between median and lateral ocelli. Temple granulose, subpolished, swollen behind eyes. Occipital carina evenly arched, reaching hypostomal carina slightly above mandible base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8036A747566C039D811B780AE37C71" blockId="42.[151,1437,1050,2013]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="B94BEAB547566C039D811B7808477F2D" bold="true" box="[199,332,1338,1364]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Mesosoma.</emphasis>
Pronotum granulose dorsally, subpolished, trans-striate below. Mesoscutum (
<figureCitation id="13042A2247566C0399F51B780C127F2D" box="[1203,1305,1338,1364]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-24@44.[178,1409,181,1939]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 28. Campoplex exareola sp. nov., female. A, fore wing; B, mesopleuron; C, propodeum; D, ovipositor; E, head, anterior view; F, head, dorsal view; G, mesoscutum; H, first metasomal segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5654013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5654013/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 28G</figureCitation>
) granulose, notauli absent. Scutellum granulose with sparse and minute punctures. Metanotum granulose. Mesopleuron (
<figureCitation id="13042A2247566C0398291B1C09CC7FE5" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-24@44.[178,1409,181,1939]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 28. Campoplex exareola sp. nov., female. A, fore wing; B, mesopleuron; C, propodeum; D, ovipositor; E, head, anterior view; F, head, dorsal view; G, mesoscutum; H, first metasomal segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5654013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5654013/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 28B</figureCitation>
) granulose with sparse and minute punctures, weakly trans-striate below tegula, speculum smooth and shiny. Metapleuron (
<figureCitation id="13042A2247566C039C711BE408967FB9" box="[311,413,1446,1472]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-24@44.[178,1409,181,1939]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 28. Campoplex exareola sp. nov., female. A, fore wing; B, mesopleuron; C, propodeum; D, ovipositor; E, head, anterior view; F, head, dorsal view; G, mesoscutum; H, first metasomal segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5654013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5654013/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 28B</figureCitation>
) granulose. Propodeum (
<figureCitation id="13042A2247566C039FFB1BE40A287FB9" box="[701,803,1446,1472]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-24@44.[178,1409,181,1939]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 28. Campoplex exareola sp. nov., female. A, fore wing; B, mesopleuron; C, propodeum; D, ovipositor; E, head, anterior view; F, head, dorsal view; G, mesoscutum; H, first metasomal segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5654013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5654013/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 28C</figureCitation>
) with area basalis triangular, long and narrow; area superomedia finely granulose, subpolished; area petiolaris weakly rugose; area superomedia confluent with area petiolaris, slightly depressed; costula absent; propodeal spiracle small and oval.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8036A747566C039D8118500BA77C0C" blockId="42.[151,1437,1050,2013]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="B94BEAB547566C039D81185008047C55" bold="true" box="[199,271,1554,1580]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Wing.</emphasis>
Fore wing (
<figureCitation id="13042A2247566C039CD3185008F17C55" box="[405,506,1554,1580]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-24@44.[178,1409,181,1939]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 28. Campoplex exareola sp. nov., female. A, fore wing; B, mesopleuron; C, propodeum; D, ovipositor; E, head, anterior view; F, head, dorsal view; G, mesoscutum; H, first metasomal segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5654013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5654013/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 28A</figureCitation>
) areolet absent. Marginal cell short, distal part of surrounding vein 2.0× longer than proximal one. Vein 1cu-a opposite M&amp;RS. External angles of second discal cell acute (70°). Hind wing with nervellus slightly inclivous, intercepted at lower 0.25.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8036A747566C039D81183C0BA27CC5" blockId="42.[151,1437,1050,2013]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="B94BEAB547566C039D81183C080D7CE1" bold="true" box="[199,262,1662,1688]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Legs.</emphasis>
Hind femur 4.6× longer than wide. Inner spur of hind tibia 0.5× as long as first tarsomere of hind tarsus. Tarsal claws pectinate basally, teeth very weak.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8036A747566C039D8118840D1A7D09" blockId="42.[151,1437,1050,2013]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="B94BEAB547566C039D81188408407C99" bold="true" box="[199,331,1734,1760]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Metasoma.</emphasis>
First metasomal segment (
<figureCitation id="13042A2247566C039F3B18840BE87C99" box="[637,739,1734,1760]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-24@44.[178,1409,181,1939]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 28. Campoplex exareola sp. nov., female. A, fore wing; B, mesopleuron; C, propodeum; D, ovipositor; E, head, anterior view; F, head, dorsal view; G, mesoscutum; H, first metasomal segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5654013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5654013/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 28H</figureCitation>
) round in cross-section of basal 0.3, without dorso-lateral carina and lateral groove. First tergite 2.5× longer than width of postpetiole. Second tergite 0.7× as long as first tergite, 1.1× longer than its apical width; thyridium oval, its distance from basal margin of tergite 1.5× its diameter. Third tergite 0.7× as long as its apical width. Sixth and seventh tergites without emarginations medially. Ovipositor sheath approx. 2.0× longer than hind femur, ovipositor (
<figureCitation id="13042A2247566C039FFA19140A297D09" box="[700,802,1878,1904]" captionStart="FIGURE 28" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1963,1987]" captionTargetBox="[178,1409,181,1939]" captionTargetId="figure-24@44.[178,1409,181,1939]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 28. Campoplex exareola sp. nov., female. A, fore wing; B, mesopleuron; C, propodeum; D, ovipositor; E, head, anterior view; F, head, dorsal view; G, mesoscutum; H, first metasomal segment." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5654013" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5654013/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Fig. 28D</figureCitation>
) gradually upcurved.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8036A747566C029D81193808BA7AAC" blockId="42.[151,1437,1050,2013]" lastBlockId="43.[151,1437,150,429]" lastPageId="43" lastPageNumber="44" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">
<emphasis id="B94BEAB547566C039D811938082B7DED" bold="true" box="[199,288,1914,1940]" pageId="42" pageNumber="43">Colour.</emphasis>
Black. Mandible except teeth, palpi and tegula yellowish brown; scape and pedicel blackish brown; all trochantellus yellow; fore leg from trochantellus on yellowish brown, coxa, trochanter and telotarsus blackish brown; mid leg with extreme base of femur, tibia media-externally and basal 0.5 of tarsus yellow, remainder of mid leg brown; hind leg with base and middle of tibia and basal 0.5 of tarsus whitish yellow, remainder of hind leg black; metasoma entirely black.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C325652C47576C029D811E9C0A817B1C" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8036A747576C029D811E9C08F77A83" blockId="43.[151,1437,150,429]" box="[199,508,222,250]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="B94BEAB547576C029D811E9C086A7A81" bold="true" box="[199,353,222,248]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry id="F328763747576C029C211E9D08A17A80" box="[359,426,223,249]" name="China" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">China</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="49FBF84547576C029CFC1E9D08FB7A83" box="[442,496,223,250]" country="China" name="Jilin" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Jilin</collectingRegion>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8036A747576C029D811F400A817B1C" blockId="43.[151,1437,150,429]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="B94BEAB547576C029D811F4008E97B65" bold="true" box="[199,482,258,284]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Comparative diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3F4D2447576C029E4C1F410AE37B64" authority="Han &amp; Achterberg &amp; Chen, 2021" authorityName="Han &amp; Achterberg &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2021" box="[778,1000,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Campoplex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="maurotrochanter" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B94BEAB547576C029E4C1F410AE37B64" box="[778,1000,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">C. maurotrochanter</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B94BEAB547576C029EB71F410D407B64" bold="true" box="[1009,1099,259,285]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A27857CE47576C029EB71F410D407B64" box="[1009,1099,259,285]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, but differs from the latter by having area petiolaris weakly rugose, propodeal median area slightly depressed, fore wing areolet absent, mid leg largely brown, and metasoma from third tergite on not compressed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C325652C47576C029D811F2D08FD7BD4" pageId="43" pageNumber="44" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8036A747576C029D811F2D08FD7BD4" blockId="43.[151,1437,150,429]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis id="B94BEAB547576C029D811F2D08457BF0" bold="true" box="[199,334,367,393]" pageId="43" pageNumber="44">Etymology.</emphasis>
Name derived from “ex-” (Latin for “out of”) and “areola” (Latin for “small open space”), because its fore wing is without areolet.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
